Config the opencv for VS2013 on the winows 8 platform
1. download the newst version of the opencv on the website;
2. Extract the zip file to the named path on the local system;
3. config the system pathï¼Œbuild an avariable of system path such as OPENCV, 
   and the values is the named path like D:\opencv2.4.13\opencv\build.Then 
   append the string value of at the end of the system path such as %OPENCV%\\x86\vc12\bin;
   The next step is to logout and login.
4. config the property mananger of VS2013, set include file to 
    D:\opencv2.4.13\opencv\build\include
    D:\opencv2.4.13\opencv\build\include\opencv,
    D:\opencv2.4.13\opencv\build\include\opencv2.And set the library file to
    D:\opencv2.4.13\opencv\build\x86\vc12\lib.The last set the Additional dependency that locate 
    at the input of Linker to the all of name from the path D:\opencv2.4.13\opencv\build\x86\vc12\lib.
    If the property mananger is debug, set the Additional dependency to the name including the char of d.
    In contrast, set the Additional dependency to the name that don't contain the char of d.
5. Finally enjoy yourself.
